doc_summary_long: The owners of Cafe Zola said they turned away two immigration agents who stopped at the Ann Arbor restaurant the afternoon of Wednesday, Aug. 9 to look for an unnamed person. Owner Alan Zakalik said two agents with U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement walked into the restaurant at 112 W. Washington Street around 2 p.m. and asked about an individual, but did not divulge the name. Zakalik was not at the restaurant at the time, but said his wife, Hediye Batu, declined to let the agents walk through the kitchen and search for the individual in question.
doc_summary_short: The owners of Cafe Zola said they turned away two immigration agents who stopped at the Ann Arbor restaurant the afternoon of Wednesday, Aug. 9 to look for an unnamed person.
doc_title: Ann Arbor restaurant refused kitchen entry to ICE agents, owner says.
